      • ERROR_INVALID_SIGNATURE

        public static final int ERROR_INVALID_SIGNATURE
        This error is returned when the signature of the OCSP-response sent by the server has an invalid signature. This should typically never happen unless the OCSP-server is compromised in someway, a fake OCSP-server is installed or something went wrong with the communication so the response was truncated.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ERROR_INVALID_SIGNERID

        public static final int ERROR_INVALID_SIGNERID
        This error is returned when the signerId in the OCSP-response sent by the server does not match the first certificate in the chain in the response. This should typically never happen unless the OCSP-server is broken.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ERROR_INVALID_SIGNERCERT

        public static final int ERROR_INVALID_SIGNERCERT
        This error is returned when the OCSP signers certificate can not be verified using the CA-certificate. This should typically never happen unless the OCSP-server is broken or compromised.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ERROR_NO_OCSP_URI

        public static final int ERROR_NO_OCSP_URI
        You did not specify a URI in the call, and there is not one embedded in the certificate.
